title: Thanos’ Fatal Flaw
body:
Thanos fucked up. Since these words haunt me when I try to sleep at night I’ve been thinking about it. A lot. Let me explain why these lines prove that Thanos’ plan, more so the snap made things worse. 

Many resources that humans, animals and some plants use are living things. Let’s look at humans for this example. I will list things that most humans use often. 

-Meat 

-Milk 

-Eggs

-Bacteria (digestions and some medicine) 

-Plants (medical uses, food, etc) 

-Fungi 

Now this definitively isn’t everything that humans use, but there is one thing that is connecting them. They come from or are living things. So that means that the populations of these were also cut in half. Due to this the whole ‘there isn’t enough resources’ is basically defeated. Basically water is all that’s left for human resources. So the human population that’s left is basically fucked because they were in basically in the same situation as before as far as resources go, but now they just have a lot more trauma. From what we’ve seen over other alien species in the MCU they also seem to fairly comparable to humans as far as resource consumption goes. So all of these populations are fucked as well. Also most animal species are fucked because their resources are mostly gone. 

So in conclusion Thanos fucked everyone over and didn’t leave anyone doing much better. They mostly just ended up having a lot of trauma. So yeah Thanos! You completely failed at your objective. Also as I’ve covered before he also killed a lot more people than his original plan talked about. So yeah, his whole plan was fucked from the beginning.  

If you liked this post go ahead and follow me at @media-theories! I post a lot of post like this covering a variety of subjects.

summary: Con una petizione si chiede un finale diverso per Avengers: Endgame
title: Con una petizione si chiede un finale diverso per Avengers: Endgame
body:
Going News | 6 giugno 2019 | cinema | di Mauro Baldan | Riproduzione riservata

Il film, diretto dai fratelli Anthony e Joe Russo, è stato distribuito in Italia lo scorso 24 aprile

[Disney]


Avengers: Endgame, il secondo film più visto di ogni tempo, superato solo da Avatar, dovrebbe avere un finale diverso. È quanto si chiede ai Marvel Studios, a cui un gruppo di sostenitori della saga cinematografica incentrata sui Vendicatori del titolo ha appena indirizzata una petizione.


Tutto ha a che fare con il personaggio interpretato da Robert Downey Jr., più esattamente una perdita che interessa Tony Stark / Iron Man, centrale in ogni film del Marvel Cinematic Universe proposto fino ad ora.


La richiesta per un finale alternativo sarebbe stata sottoscritta da oltre 36mila appassionati della saga.

blog.name: cometsweepandleonidsfly
blog.title: comets weep & leonids fly
blog.description:
Home is where one starts from. As we grow older
The world becomes stranger, the pattern more complicated
Of dead and living. Not the intense moment
Isolated, with no before and after,
But a lifetime burning in every moment
...
Love is most nearly itself
When here and now cease to matter.
--T.S. Eliot, "East Coker"
